article.description: Emily Carter scored 22 points but had her streak of consecutive free throws made snapped at 60 as Texas Christian (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) coasted to 83-59 victory over Texas-San Antonio on Friday night.
article.headline: Emily Carter scores 22 to lift Horned Frogs over Texas-San Antonio
article.linkText: Carter gets 22 to lift TCU by Texas-San Antonio
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO --  Emily Carter scored 22 points but had her streak of consecutive free throws made snapped at 60 as Texas Christian (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) coasted to 83-59 victory over Texas-San Antonio on Friday night.

Helena Sverrisdottir added 18 points, and Starr Crawford had 17 points and 12 rebounds for the Horned Frogs (3-0).

Alysse Davis paced the Roadrunners (2-1) with 19 points and Amber Gregg added 13.

TCU pulled away in the last 10 minutes of the first half utilizing a zone defense that kept the Roadrunners from getting into any type of rhythm.

Carter, who had gone eight straight games without missing a free throw, hit her first 10 attempts from the stripe before missing Friday. She's tied for second all-time behind Richmond's Ginny Doyle, who hit 66 straight free throws from 1991-92.
